@startuml contributions-summary-overview
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial

title Thesis Contributions Summary

rectangle "**Pedagogical Mapping\nContribution**" as PED #D5F5E3 {
  note as PED_N
  * Digital transformation of physical
    classroom card-sorting experiments
  * Systematic HPC-to-game-mechanic mapping
    (threads -> players, shared memory ->
    shared container, TLS -> private buffers)
  * Serious game as icebreaker for
    abstract parallel computing concepts
  end note
}

rectangle "**Technical Architecture\nContribution**" as ARCH #D4E6F1 {
  note as ARCH_N
  * Extension-based architecture
    (CardManager -> MultiplayerCardManager)
  * HTTP/SSE relay for browser-first
    multiplayer (no WebRTC dependency)
  * GDSync web-export patch strategy
    (intercept + replace transport layer)
  * Barrier synchronization game mechanic
  end note
}

rectangle "**Validation & Evaluation\nContribution**" as EVAL #FCF3CF {
  note as EVAL_N
  * Classroom deployment with
    undergraduate students
  * Usability evaluation (SUS/Likert)
  * Engagement evidence collection
  * Cross-browser performance testing
  * Open-source artifact for reuse
  end note
}

PED -[#27AE60,bold]-> ARCH : pedagogical\nrequirements\nshaped architecture
ARCH -[#2E86C1,bold]-> EVAL : technical artifact\nenabled validation
EVAL -[#F39C12,bold,dashed]-> PED : feedback informs\nfuture iterations

note bottom
All three contribution areas converge in the
HPC Sorting Serious Game: a web-first educational
tool for teaching parallel computing through play.
end note

@enduml
